    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Free Speech Bias?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Marshal A Phillips letter objects to boycotting advertisers that have withdrawn spots from Laura Schlesinger's talk show because they refuse to be associated with her controversial view of gays as biological deviants (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A writer (letter, May 24) urges consumers to boycott products from companies that have withdrawn their advertising from Paramount Television's forthcoming talk show featuring Dr. Laura Schlessinger, because such advertisers should be punished for refusing to be linked with her controversial views of gays as biological deviants.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A writer (letter, May 24) urges consumers to boycott products from companies that have withdrawn their advertising from Paramount Television's forthcoming talk show featuring Dr. Laura Schlessinger, because such advertisers should be punished for refusing to be linked with her controversial views of gays as biological deviants.</p>
        <p>Would the writer be equally supportive of Paramount's forum for free speech if it produced shows condemning and vilifying immigrants, Jews, blacks, Asians or Latinos?</p>
        <p>MARSHAL A. PHILLIPS  Los Angeles, May 24, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
